This article is a press briefing by White House Press Secretary Jay Carney on July 29, 2011. Carney introduces Ron Bloom, Assistant to the President for Manufacturing Policy, and Heather Zichal, Deputy Assistant to the President for Energy Policy, who discuss the historic agreement reached on fuel economy. The agreement aims to nearly double fuel economy to 54.5 miles per gallon for cars and light-duty trucks by 2025. The article also includes a Q&A session where Carney addresses concerns about vehicle safety, economic impact, and job creation. Carney emphasizes the importance of compromise and the need for a bipartisan solution to the debt ceiling issue. He also mentions that the President is engaged in conversations with lawmakers and other stakeholders to find a resolution.